                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77/52d.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may inform the Government of Panama that the Secretary will arrive at Colon
                    on the morning of February 27, and will proceed to Panama the same day. He will
                    leave Panama on the morning of the 29th, recross the Isthmus, and proceed to
                    Costa Rica.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
